| World's Largest Fossil Forest, and One of the Oldest               |
|   from the like-insects-in-amber dept.                             |
|   posted by kdawson on Monday April 30, @20:14 (Science)           |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/30/2250255      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

solitas writes in with news from last week of the [0]discovery of a
fossilized forest in Illinois. The forest was found in the ceiling of a
working coal mine, 250 feet below the surface. It was drowned 300 million
years ago in an earthquake, its discoverers speculate — here is a
[1]graphic of its formation. Geologists are excited because the huge
fossilized forest, over 25 square miles in extent, preserves trees and
other plants upright, as they grew.

Discuss this story at:
    http://science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/30/2250255

