| Exposing Bots In Big Companies                                     |
|   from the pwned dept.                                             |
|   posted by kdawson on Monday April 30, @22:24 (Security)          |
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/30/2340255           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]CalicoPenny let us know about yet another "30 days" effort, this one
to name the names of [1]major companies infected with spam-spewing bots.
[2]Support Intelligence began the effort on March 28, out of frustration
at not being able to attract the attention of anyone who could fix the
problems at these companies. While they haven't named 30 companies over
the ensuing month, they did name some prominent ones, such as Thompson
Financial, Bank of America, and AIG. The scary part is that if a bot can
spam it can capture keystrokes or troll for interesting documents.

