denebian devil writes "In an Editorial/Blog at ITPRO, Davey Winder writes
of a keynote speech at Infosecurity Europe by Member of Parliament Derek
Wyatt. In this speech, which was about the IT security demands of running
the 2012 London Olympics, Derek Wyatt MP dropped the bombshell that IT
Security at the Olympics will hinge not on which companies show
themselves to be the best in their field or to have the technology that
best meets the needs of the Olympics, but rather on [0]whether or not the
companies were a 'major sponsor' of the Olympics. So who has bought their
way into being the security experts of choice, and with whom our security
and that of the visiting millions will rest? Visa."

